overview: The user wanted to enhance their Sleep Questionnaire Application by
  adding a database for storing responses, an admin dashboard for client access,
  and an authentication system. The project began with an evaluation of the
  existing codebase against the provided Statement of Work. Key decisions
  included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for database management and
  opting for a simple password-based authentication system. The implementation
  involved updating the demographic data structure, creating a
   model in Prisma, developing API endpoints for saving
  and retrieving data (including CSV export), and building a basic admin
  dashboard with login functionality. The authentication was streamlined by
  leveraging Next.js middleware to protect routes, simplifying the session
  management. The questionnaire form was modified to submit data to the new API
  endpoint. The process included detailed instructions for database setup and a
  comprehensive testing phase to ensure all new functionalities worked as
  expected, including debugging the form submission flow.
